Dia. 02 Opponent's Vital Point
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White can't capture Black if he simply takes at 1, because Black can play the vital point at 2.
\par
\par The proverb which says "\cf1\b The opponent's vital point is my vital point\cf0\b0 " works very well.
\par
\par Actually if Black blocks at A instead of 2, it is also good.
\par
\par
\par }
