Dia. 03 Variation/Pae
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par However if there is a White stone at \'a1\'e2, it is not good to block at 1.
\par
\par If Black plays like that, White's attachment at 2 is severe. It is also the \cf1\b 1-2 vital point\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par Black has to start the pae with 3. It is always important to pay attention of the outside liberties.
\par }
